# Data Rules

## Brief introduction
These rules keep data schema naming and model mapping consistent across projects. Use semantic names, explicit types, and migration-safe changes.

- Use stable naming conventions for entities and fields
- Prefer additive migrations; avoid destructive schema changes without migration notes
- Keep DTO/domain mapping explicit in feature data layer
- Document breaking data changes in `docs/data/`
